Feature: nullfield_variant_writeback — the full mutation cycle of a `variant | null` struct field

  # Match `b.f`, write `null` back, re-match (the `null` arm), write a case value back, re-match (the
  # case arm) — each stage adds a distinct amount so the exit code witnesses every write:
  # A{x=30} -> +30 ; b.f = null -> +2 ; b.f = B{y=10} -> +10 ; total 42.

  Scenario: mutate a null-union field value -> null -> value and re-match each stage
    When built and run
    Then exit = 42
